<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870423-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Purolator Courier StakeLowered to 4.5% by Group</HL><DD> 04/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PCCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   An investment group including FMR Corp. and Fidelity International Ltd. said it lowered its stake in Purolator Courier Corp. to 4.5%.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, the group said it sold 216,500 common shares April 14 through April 16 at $39.375 to $39.50 each.    The group now holds 343,900 shares in the Basking Ridge, N.J., package-delivery and auto-parts company. No reason was given for the reduction.    On April 14, Purolator endorsed a $306 million purchase proposal from Emery Air Freight Corp., an air freight transportation concern based in Wilton, Conn.    Officials of FMR, a Boston-based holding company, couldn't be reached for comment. Fidelity is a Hamilton, Bermuda-based investment advisory firm. </TEXT></DOC>